I have to say, I was so disappointed with myself that I didn't manage to do this on two days. Feeling very low on confidence anyhow at the moment, that didn't help.

But then I remembered Adriene's words from a previous journey, where she said something along the lines of "imagine that right now, you are exactly where you need to be" and then I realized that now, slightly behind everyone else, the practices suddenly perfectly align with my days. Yesterday where I could only do it in the late evening, there was the lovely snuggly practice to send me off to bed. Today, where I had time and feeling unusually active (even went for a run for the first time this year), there's this beautiful, slightly longer practice.

And as confidence was lagging again during the twist when I saw my skin folds, I said to myself "But look, how strong I am! I am so strong!" and I lifted the corners of my mouth and all was well.

And the mantra "My breath is my anchor, my anchor is my breath" has really become a tool for me. A crutch I use when I am feeling weak or unfocused, I use it to draw me back in.

Thank you so much Adriene for being there, catching me when I fall and making life so much brighter. Namaste. ‚ù§Ô∏è
